title: If That Were Me
lyric: Where do they go and what do they do? They're walking on by. They're looking at you. Some people stop, some people stare. But would they help you and do they care?   How did you fall? Did you fall at all? Are you happy when you are sleeping underneath the stars? When it's cold is it your hope that keeps you warm?   A spare bit of change is all that I give. Is it lonely where you are sleeping in between parked cars? When it thunders where do you hide from the storm?   Could you ever forgive my self-pity? They're walking on by. They're looking at you.    (Melanie ChisholmRick Nowels)
